Sentencas: Symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell (S-SOFC) has gained extensive attention for its simplifying fabrication process and reducing cost.
Titulo: Enhancing the catalytic activity of PrBaFe2O5+δ double perovskite with BaCoO3-δ modification as an electrode material for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Fe-based double perovskite PrBaFe2O5+delta (PBF) is a potential electrode material for S-SOFC due to the excellent mixed electronic and oxygen ionic conductivity.
Titulo: Enhancing the catalytic activity of PrBaFe2O5+δ double perovskite with BaCoO3-δ modification as an electrode material for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: However, the electrochemical performance of PBF is limited by lacking enough oxygen vacancies and the sluggish oxygen-ion transport kinetics.
Titulo: Enhancing the catalytic activity of PrBaFe2O5+δ double perovskite with BaCoO3-δ modification as an electrode material for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Herein, a BaCoO3-delta(BCO) impregnated PBF (PBF-BCO) electrode is investigated with enhanced catalytic activity.
Titulo: Enhancing the catalytic activity of PrBaFe2O5+δ double perovskite with BaCoO3-δ modification as an electrode material for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The BCO decoration can significantly decrease the polarization resistance (Rp) by approximately 36.5% and 26.0% compared to PBF at 800 degrees C in air and hydrogen atmosphere, respectively.
Titulo: Enhancing the catalytic activity of PrBaFe2O5+δ double perovskite with BaCoO3-δ modification as an electrode material for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The peak power density (PPD) of an electrolyte-supported S-SOFC with PBF-BCO electrode is nearly 36% higher than that of PBF electrode.
Titulo: Enhancing the catalytic activity of PrBaFe2O5+δ double perovskite with BaCoO3-δ modification as an electrode material for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The prominent electrochemical performance of the PBF-BCO electrode is attributed to the significantly accelerated oxygen adsorption/dissociation processes, which promote the oxygen reduction reactions (ORR) and enhanced charge transfer processes in H2 atmosphere for superior hydrogen oxidation reaction (HOR).
Titulo: Enhancing the catalytic activity of PrBaFe2O5+δ double perovskite with BaCoO3-δ modification as an electrode material for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results demonstrate that the BCO impregnated PBF is one of the promising electrode materials for S-SOFC.
Titulo: Enhancing the catalytic activity of PrBaFe2O5+δ double perovskite with BaCoO3-δ modification as an electrode material for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells
